        [
          "Assamite Warrior embraced since the Schism, has only known the Camarilla as your home.",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "Jenn Wolfe"
        ],
        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "You grew up just outside of Pittsburgh, in the heart of the Rust Belt where jobs became fewer and the only way out for a small town kid like you was to put yourself in debt in college or join the Army. You chose the latter. You grew up like all the kids in your area hunting, and that skill set was put to use by the Army. Your keen eye and steady hand made you a perfect sniper and earned you a ticket to Afghanistan, where your unique talents were put to use by the Army. You don't talk about it much, though, most of it will be classified forever. But that didn't mean your talents went unnoticed.\n\nYour tour done, you returned home and wondered what civilian life would hold. You never got to find out, as you barely got home before you were embraced. The world as you knew it got a whole hell of a lot more complicated. Your sire was an assassin too, a Muslim one, who had been forced to flee from his home because of \"political disputes\". A refugee, he came to America and the Camarilla, hoping to flee what he knows is coming and keep alive the dream of Haqim and preserve the truth of the blood. You were one of his first steps in doing that, an American soldier with the heart of a fighter, not tied to what he saw as the corrupt ways of Ur-Shulgi. You would fight to keep the true dream alive.\n\nFrankly, you don't know if any of that is even true. In the years since your Embrace, you have gotten to know the others of your Clan and know there is at least some truth to some of the stories, but all of it sounds too surreal to be believed. You are a warrior, someone amazing with a gun and you know how to use it, that world you know and understand. You've clung to that. But there is a crazier world out there, one in which you may be a vampire but you are by far not the top of the food chain. Your people are hunted by the Assamites in the Mountain, there are elders who use the younger vampires as pawns, and and now there are rumors of humans hunting everyone. You came home from a war to be stuck in the middle of this, and you have to wonder if it's worth it. In any case, you've heard Los Angeles is a relatively safe place for the Assamites to live, and you've heard of other crazy things about this city too. It may not be home, but at least it's not Afghanistan either...right?"
        ],
        [
          "Sire:",
          "Vasily Petrovich",
          "Reference: (If any)",
          "",
          "",
